node.text: So much talent and beauty in one place. Honored🔥🙌

It was an honour to work on this anthology with so many strong voices ♡
Thank you @her.red.pen.wordsmithing @candicedaquin @kindra_m_austin  and Thank you to @toi.magazine for this feature °•♡*
・・・
"We Will Not Be Silenced" is a book written by over 90 sexual assault survivors of abuse in one's childhood, rape, sexual harassment, etc. ·
·
It is a TRULY powerful book that will help anyone who has been sexually assaulted to know that the feelings of -Shame
-Guilt
-Depression
-Confusion
-Anger
are real and your feelings are valid. ·
·
If you can relate to this, let us know if you are comfortable doing so. ·
Our Apr/May issue (link in bio) has the full interview of the authors of WWNBS. ·
·
Book can be purchased on Amazon. To get from free if you cannot afford it at this time, email indieblucollective@gmail.com
·
#toimagazine #sexualassault #saam #sexualassaultsurvivor #eatingdisorderrecovery #anger #childhoodtrauma #narcissisticabuse #addiction #metoo #childabuse #bethechange #healing #recovery

It took me over 40 years but I spoke out & the first thing he said when police knocked on his door was '  I've been expecting you for 40 years'  He got a 12 year sentence and the young child in me was set free.  Never too late to speak up

I am up to my eyeballs right now in intense therapy for all the horrific abuse I suffered. I will never have justice because for one, my mother is dead and for two, one of my sexual abusers is insulated within his career and will never be held accountable. I suffer night terrors, extreme anxiety, ptsd and deep, deep fears. I have serious medical issues because I held it all inside and it manifested physically because my emotions could no longer deal with it all. I am not a victim any longer. I am writing a book as well about my life, my struggles and my victories because my voice deserves to be heard and I want other women to KNOW they matter and they can overcome this type of horror.  I hear you, I feel you and I stand with you all. 💖
All of this resonates. I can completely identify with each person that made a statement here. Thank you ♥️
My poem is on page 260: Wayward Daughter.

Thank you for featuring this and sharing our important work. I have two poems in this collection. I'm currently working through the aftermath of my sexual assault, molestation as a child, and abuse, and it is relentless and affects every aspect of my life.
So much talent and beauty in one place. Honored🔥🙌
